# keys/ — this deployment's own GPG public keys

This directory holds the GPG (GNU Privacy Guard) **public** keys that THIS deployment
(`__PROJECT_NAME__`, scaffolded __CREATED_AT__) trusts for its own SIGNED commissions
(`./verify-commission`, design/GPG-TRUST-LAYER.md §3 in the autoharn checkout this
deployment was scaffolded from) and any future signed chain-head verification
(`./verify-chain`, §4). It is deliberately separate from autoharn's own `law/keys/`, which
verifies only autoharn's own `ratified/*` git tags on the autoharn repository itself and has
no bearing on this deployment — commit YOUR OWN signing key here, never there. See
design/GPG-TRUST-LAYER-FAQ.md §3 (in the autoharn checkout) for the full two-domain split
and the exact commit ceremony for each.

## Current state: AWAITING-KEY

No public key has been committed to this directory yet. This is the honest empty state, not
an error: `verify-commission` reports the distinct refusal `NO-COMMITTED-KEY` (exit 3) for
any commission that carries a banked `.claude/commission-<id>.asc` signature but finds this
directory empty — loud, never a silent pass, and never confused with an actual forged
signature (`FORGED-OR-CORRUPT`, a different, checkable fact: a committed key exists here and
the signature does not match it).

## What lands here once a key exists

- `<name>.asc` — the public half of a keypair generated with `gpg --full-generate-key`
  (Ed25519 recommended, matching every throwaway test key this layer was witnessed with),
  exported with `gpg --armor --export <fingerprint> > keys/<name>.asc` and committed
  alongside `deployment.json` (or otherwise kept next to it, if this deployment is not
  itself version-controlled).
- The **private** key and any **revocation certificate** never belong here — print the
  revocation certificate and store it offline, away from both this deployment and the
  signing key itself; see design/GPG-TRUST-LAYER-FAQ.md §2 for why.

